      "gap_id": "gap-bor-scaffold-001",
      "description": "The Bill of Rights remains a scaffold awaiting human authorship, leaving the DIO without a defined constitutional perimeter (scope of enterprise, prohibited activities, core identity, etc.).",
      "mission_ref": "BoR § Articles I–VI; MSP § Purpose, § Relationship to the Bill of Rights",
      "priority": "critical",
      "rationale": "Without an authored BoR, Arbiter (#190) cannot enforce any scope boundary, and the MSP has no constitutional foundation to translate into operational rules. The entire governance chain is inoperative, making every action permissible by default."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "gap-msp-empty-rules-002",
      "description": "The MSP bootstrap seed contains no rules; the DIO operates under default-permissive MSP evaluation, meaning any Action Proposal passes the MSP+genome compliance gate without scrutiny.",
      "mission_ref": "MSP § Rules, § Purpose (two-gate compliance)",
      "priority": "high",
      "rationale": "Nomos (#200) is effectively disabled as a policy enforcement point. Any AP—including potentially dangerous or scope-expanding actions—is authorized, creating significant operational risk and undermining the governance architecture."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "gap-senate-inactive-003",
      "description": "No substantive MSP rules have been published by Senate through the PEM→review→Rollout pipeline, despite the Senate being the sole authority for MSP amendments.",
      "mission_ref": "MSP § Authority, § Amendment Protocol",
      "priority": "high",
      "rationale": "The DIO remains in a perpetual bootstrap state with no governance evolution. The Senate’s inaction means no rules are generated from policy exceptions (PEMs), and the mission statement does not reflect operational reality."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "gap-goal-mission-drift-004",
      "description": "Dispatched goals reference MSP sections that do not exist (e.g., 'MSP §critical-priority', '§high-priority'), indicating goals are being generated without alignment to actual mission rules.",
      "mission_ref": "MSP § Rules (empty), Recent Goals list",
      "priority": "medium",
      "rationale": "Goals that claim mission grounding in non-existent MSP sections create mission drift. While not immediately dangerous, they waste execution capacity and erode trust in the goal-setting process. This gap will become more severe when real rules are introduced and goal references become stale or contradictory."
    }
  ]
}

